WICHITA, Kan. (KWCH) - The Kansas Board of Education did not approve Gov. Laura Kelly‚Äôs order to delay the opening of schools until after Labor Day.

The board voted 5 to 5 on the executive order, but it needed a simple majority, to pass.

The decision on when to reopen schools now goes back to school district.

WICHITA, Kan. (KWCH) - The Kansas Board of Education did not approve Gov. Laura Kelly‚Äôs order to delay the opening of schools until after Labor Day.

The board voted 5 to 5 on the executive order, but it needed a simple majority, to pass.

The decision on when to reopen schools now goes back to school district.

post_text:
We have now completed week two of our Continuous Learning Plan. We know this is a difficult time for everyone.
We want to thank our families for being so patient and flexible. If we can help you, please let us know. Out staff has done a remarkable job and wants to continue to serve our students. As a reminder, we are serving lunches on Monday and Thursday, from 10:00 am until noon for children ages 1-18. Meals can be picked up curbside in the parking lot West of the High School. We will have our regularly scheduled Board of Education Meeting this coming Monday, April 13th, at 7:00 pm in the Middle School Auditorium. Due to social distancing recommendations, we will not be inviting guests, but we will stream the meeting through our Facebook account. The board agenda is posted on our school website, www.usd311.com. Thank you for your support of our staff and students. The buildings have closed, but learning continues. Stay safe! Go Bulldogs!!

post_text: Whew, one week is complete of the Continuous Learning Plan. We are so appreciative to have the support of our families and community as we continue to retool our educational process. We know this week has been stressful and certainly a learning experience. We are blessed with hardworking, creative, and passionate staff members who want to provide a great educational experience. Please feel free to provide feedback to your child's teacher. To better serve our students and families, we will continue to reach out and determine what is and is not working. Next week families will be contacted by office staff to "check in" and gain even more feedback. Please let us know if we can help in any way. Stay safe. Go BULLDOGS!!

post_text: Congratulations to our track athletes on a great season. Timber Allen set a new school record in Javelin throwing 166 feet and 7 inches. He won the regional meet and will be representing PPHS at state. He qualified in the shot put and discus as well. Coach Jon Johnson lost a wager with Timber and wore a kilt for the remainder of the meet (picture coming soon). Brock Steadman jumped 6 feet 2 inches in the high jump to qualify for state. Jorah Harbaugh got sweet revenge and defeated her nemesis from South Barber and qualified for state placing third in the 800 meters. Abby White qualified in the 300 meter hurdles. The 4x800 meter relay team of Jorah Harbaugh, Gabi Unruh, Abby White and McKenna Vogl also qualified.

post_text: Unfortunately our music room was vandalized this weekend. Many instruments were destroyed or damaged. We are working with the Reno County Sheriff‚Äôs Office and our music room is still off limits. We hope to have our insurance agent here on Monday to help us assess the damage. All 5-12 music students will meet in the auditorium for class. As awful as this is for our students, we are working to provide them with instruments as soon as we can. A silver lining, and hopefully a life lesson for our students, is they/we are not in this alone. The outpouring of support has been tremendous. I have received many emails and calls of support and willingness to help. I have a special thank you to Joan Simenou, Superintendent of Burrton Schools, who has been attempting to help us find replacement instruments and has volunteered to help us restore our room when we can. BULLDOGS WE‚ÄôVE GOT THIS!!!!!!!!!

KSHSAA Sportsmanship guidelines:

Art. 1: SPORTSMANSHIP is a general way of thinking and behaving. The following sportsmanship policy items are listed below for clarification:
a. Be courteous to all (participants, coaches, officials,
staff and fans).
b. Know the rules, abide by and respect the official‚Äôs
decisions.
c. Win with character and lose with dignity.
d. Display appreciation for good performance regardless
of the team.
e. Exercise self-control and reflect positively upon
yourself, team and school.
f. Permit only positive sportsmanlike behavior to reflect on
your school or its activities.
